PHASE 3: CODE COMPARISON — Research Code vs Our Codebase
=========================================================

FEATURE               | RESEARCH CODE         | OUR CODE (energivanu)    | BETTER
----------------------|-----------------------|-------------------------|--------
Num features          | 9                     | 18-34 (FeatureStore)    | ✅ OURS
Window size           | 120 steps (10 min)    | 60-120 steps            | ✅ MATCH
Horizon               | 120 steps (10 min)    | 60-120 steps            | ✅ MATCH
Positional encoding   | Sinusoidal PE         | Learned param (randn)   | ⚠️ SINUSOIDAL BETTER
Feature embedding     | Linear → ReLU         | PatchEmbed (patches)    | ✅ OURS (novel)
Encoder               | TransformerEncoder×6  | TransformerEncoder×6    | ✅ MATCH
Attention heads       | 8                     | 4-8                     | ✅ MATCH
Gated Residual Net    | GRN present           | GRN present             | ✅ MATCH
Frequency branch      | NOT present           | FreqBranch (FFT)        | ✅ OURS (superior)
Dual output head      | Power + Signal        | Power + Signal          | ✅ MATCH
Loss function         | Spike-weighted MSE    | Asymmetric SpikeLoss    | ✅ MATCH (sophisticated)
Classification loss   | CrossEntropy          | Weighted CrossEntropy   | ✅ OURS (5:1:2 weights)
Signal generator      | BatterySignalGenerator| SignalEngine            | ✅ MATCH
Co-optimization       | NOT present           | CoOptimizer + Job/Pri   | ✅ OURS (unique)
Data generation       | Simple numpy          | Sophisticated simulation| ✅ OURS (30-day realistic)
Checkpointing         | NOT present           | Best val checkpoint     | ✅ OURS
LR scheduling         | CosineAnnealing       | Warmup + Cosine         | ✅ OURS
Gradient clipping     | max_norm=1.0          | grad_clip=1.0           | ✅ MATCH
Early stopping        | NOT present           | Patience-based          | ✅ OURS
Inference engine      | ColossusInferenceEng  | SignalEngine only       | ⚠️ NEED UPGRADE
Model interpretability| NOT present           | NOT present             | ⚠️ BOTH MISSING
Live sensor API       | NOT implemented       | NOT implemented         | ⚠️ BOTH MISSING
Real weather API      | NOT implemented       | NOT implemented         | ⚠️ BOTH MISSING
Multi-cluster support | NOT present           | NOT present             | ⚠️ BOTH MISSING

KEY INSIGHT: Our code is ALREADY more sophisticated than the research code in most dimensions.
The research code is a SIMPLER reference implementation. Our gaps are:
  1. No sinusoidal positional encoding (we use learned — sinusoidal is better for extrapolation)
  2. No proper inference engine for production deployment
  3. No real sensor/weather API integration
  4. No model interpretability
  5. No multi-cluster (global) training support
